review_blob: This was way to sweet.  Gross and sweet.  Why someone would call it a beer, I dont know.

Well i was surprised.  Thought it would taste either like nothing or way to sweet.  Nicely in between and only tasted that freshness from the watermelon rind on the way down.  Definitely can only drink on a nice summer day.
Not bad at all!  Watered down a little, but the hint of coffee makes up for it.
Golden color with a slight bite to it.  Okay, glad to have tried, but wont need to buy again.
Dark amber. Tastes like wood.  Gross.  Dont know if Id want to try other Red Oaks- they might all taste like Oak.
I was amazed that I could actually drink it- assumed it would be sicky sweet.  Dont think I would want a whole pack, but a single every now and then is likely a good choice.
beer_name: Fort Collins Major Toms Pomegranate Wheat

review_blob: I dont like IPAs but if I had to choose one to drink for the rest of my life, it would be this one.  A pleasant surprise from a regular IPA, I suppose.
Not really my favorite, but not awful.  A little smoky dark tasting for my preference.  Dont need to get again.
A new favorite lager.  Will buy again and again.  Crisp, light, and makes me happy when I want something simple.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Pure Brewed Organic Lager

review_blob: Definitely not bad.  Wasnt sure what to expect at all, but would buy again.  Light, a little sweet.  I forget much about it now though...had it last week.  Ill have to come back and edit again.
I enjoy a good pale ale now and again, and this was a good pale ale for now.  Like it and would buy again.
Not bad at all- but probably not something I would buy again if I had the choice.  Tastes like a lager, a little dark, but also a bit watery for my taste.  A strange mixture...
No no no no no!  Sicky sweet- may as well be juice.    Cant say it doesnt have taste... but its definitely not a good one.  Glad I bought it as a single.
Tastes like an IPA to me.  Just with less of a skunk to it.  Not a favorite.  Not much going on in it.
Its okay... cant find the spice flavors from the bottle.  Very light.  Think its another case of one of a pretty bottle lacking in taste.
Good stuff.  Just my kind of dark beer.  Full taste without bitterness,  Similar to Smithwicks.
Good and tasty, light and airy.  Pretty good for a hot Carolina day.  Slight sweetness, light beer taste.
Fresh and clean taste, can definitely tell it is a golden ale.  BUT... kind of blah.  I might only buy it if there was nothing else at the store.  Good, but otherwise ho hum.
beer_name: Flying Dog Tire Bite Golden Ale

review_blob: ewewewew... took a sip thinking lager meant, well, lager.  ended up pouring it out, seeing how pink it was, and gave the rest of the 6-pack to my girlfriend who only drinks wine and mixed drinks.  worked out, but i was down a six pack. bummer.
Though they were jut making this to make it... but its really got a good smooth finish with golden taste.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

review_blob: Good post-pumpkin flavor.  Too too heavy or sweet.  But dont drink with food... gross... very good if you drink alone in the midst of the fall.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Yum- a little sweet, but still gives a nice refreshing swig.  It is one of my "regulars" for the fridge.

Maybe it was because I was really looking for a refreshing swig or maybe its because its not a good lunchtime brew, but BOY is this strong for what I expected.  But, as usually happens, I got used to the taste and strength and it was great to wash down some garlic crackers with.  Too skunky for me in the aftertaste, though, and doubt I will purchase again.
UPDATED: APR 3, 2009
beer_name: Sea Dog Wild Blueberry Wheat Ale

review_blob: I really thought there would be a better, more sweet fruity flavor to this.  Unfortunately no... and it took a bit to get used to the sort of bitter, ick aftertaste of the passion fruit.  After I got used to it, it wasnt terrible, but certainly wasnt anything special- especially not for a limited release.

Left a little sticky, morning breath-esque taste in the mouth post drink, but during each sip the flavor of apricots was good (definitely could taste the apricot!), thogh I wish it was more refreshing and less sweet.
UPDATED: APR 3, 2009
Hoppy!  Not too much, though, so I can stand it!  Not a refresher... good with dinner... like hamburgers!  Yum.
A bit skunky for my taste, but wasnt bothered by it through the entire beer as I usually am with skunky beers.  Also pretty watery, which seemed to enhance that skunk.
Thick wheat taste at first, but becomes more subtle as you drink it.  I thought it wouldnt be as wheaty as it is, as I enjoy lighter wheat beers, but it wasnt a bother after a few sips.
Strawberry taste only noticeable after some food.  Very light lager and very sweet strawberry taste.  Could be refreshing...
Ew.  Its too carbonated, too light, and too skunky, as many other have said.  Its not my kind of refreshing beer.  It reminds me more of stale seltzer water.
Not too much raspberry to make it bitter.  Just enough to make it a lighter fruit beer.  Had it from the bottle, so I enjoyed it more than I feel I would have with draft.
The raspberry flavor is apparent in the bitter aftertaste, but definitely not any hint of a fruity taste, as I had hoped for.  Not my favorite, as the bitterness kind of killed it for me.
Too much like a carbonated dessert wine for me.  Tart cherry.  Good if I was in the mood for something other than beer.  Would give me a tummy ache, like malt beverages (a la Smirnoff).  Eww.
A bit bitter for my taste.  Also pretty watery... just okay on my standards for an IPA.
Dark, yet smooth with a bit of a bitter aftertaste on the way down.  Good when in the mood for a dark beer.
Dark, thick, rich.  Good when in the mood for a smooth dark beer without the bitter aftertaste.  Looks like tar, though!
I prefer sans orange slice.  Nice light and fruity brew... able to have a few without the sweet flavoring become too intense.
Pretty light.  Refreshing, as are most beers I like.  A tad sweet on the way down, a tad hoppy aftertaste.  Yummy!
Why did they make this beer when I get water for free out of my sink?  Gross!  I cant believe I had to pay for this...
Super refreshing.  Perfect for after a long summer day... or in a smoky casino.  Smooth.  Light.
I like lagers, but this was what I called an armpit beer.  It tastes like an armpit smells.  Expecting it to be refreshing, I was sadly disappointed.  I need something more smooth.
Not bad, but definitely need to be in the mood to taste a lot of wheat.  Rich and thick for a wheat beer.
Only in draft.  Delicious rich apricot flavor... a little more than just a hint of apricot.
UPDATED: OCT 27, 2008

Delicious aroma and flavor of apricots.  Wonderful for a refreshing pick-me-up.  The guy at the bottle shop said that this was the best apricot wheat he had tried (which has been a lot, for what there is), and I would say I can definitely believe that.

Strangely, the first time I tasted this on draft it was difficult to taste any hint of strawberry.  Upon more recently drinking from a bottle, I found there to be enough strawberry taste.  I would not have been able to drink more than one at a time due to the strawberry-ness.  Though not too much, there was enough for it to be difficult to stomach too many of.
A nice pale ale with a hint of nut.  Good for a refresher, but also good enough if in the mood for a bit of a heavier ale.
Refreshing with just enough of a cherry aftertaste, while leaving you satisfied and able to drink more
